  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN129.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭai vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What was said to HER who was changed in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN129.2">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>uḷḷal vēṇṭu moḻinta piṉṉeṉa</l>
                <l><supplied>na</supplied>ḷḷeṉ kaṅku ṉaṭuṅkutuṇai yāyavar</l>
                <l>niṉmaṟan tuṟaital yāvatu puṉmaṟan</l>
                <l>talaṅkal vāṉkaḻai yutirneṉ ṉōkkik</l>
                <l>kalaipiṇai viḷikkuṅ kāṉat tāṅkaṭ</l>
                <l>kalcēr pirunta katuvāyk kurampait</l>
                <l>tāḻimutaṟ kalitta kōḻilaip paruti</l>
                <l>potivayiṟ ṟiḷaṅkāy pēṭai yūṭṭip</l>
                <l>pōkilpiḷan tiṭṭa poṅkal veṇ<supplied>kā</supplied>ḻ</l>
                <l>nalkūr peṇṭi ralkutaṟ kūṭṭuṅ</l>
                <l>kalaṅkumuṉaic cīṟūr kaitalai vaippak</l>
                <l>koḻuppā <supplied>ti</supplied>ṉṟa koḻumpaṭai maḻavar</l>
                <l>ceruppuṭai yaṭiyar teṇcuṉai maṇṭu</l>
                <l>maruñcura mariya valla vārkōṟ</l>
                <l>ṟiruntiḻaip paṇaittōṭ ṭēṉāṟu katuppiṟ</l>
                <l>kuvaḷai yuṇka <supplied>ṇi</supplied>vaḷoṭu celaṟkeṉa</l>
                <l>neñcuvā yaviḻntaṉar kātala</l>
                <l>rañci lōti yāyiḻai namakkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>He who was a trembling companion in the deepest night,</l>
                <l>saying “[I] must remember after [you] have stayed behind”, (1f.)</l>
                <l>– to us with choice jewels [and] pretty fine hair – (18)</l> 
                <l>how can he stay [away], forgetting you? (3a-c)</l>
                <l>[Our] lover opened up in [his] heart, saying (17)</l>
                <l>“the difficult deserts, (14a)</l>
                <l>where the warriors with rich weapons who have eaten fat cow [meat]</l>
                <l>rush to the clear mountain pools, [their] feet in sandals, (12f.)</l>
                <l>while [the people from] the little villages put [their] hands on [their] heads, (11)</l> 
                <l>[villages], where the dwelling of poor women joins</l>
                <l>white wooly kernels split [and] put down by birds</l>
                <l>after feeding [their] females with the young, unripe fruits with roomy belly(?)</l>
                <l>with a circle of fat leaves swollen in jars</l>
                <l>in diminutive huts sitting among the rocks, (6-10)</l>
                <l>in that place in the forest, where the stag calls out for [his] doe,</l>
                <l>looking at the paddy shed by the swaying sky bamboo, forgetting about the grass, (3d-5)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">are not [too] difficult (14bc)</l>
                <l>to go with her with waterlily kajal eyes,</l>
                <l>honey-scented hair, bamboo shoulders [and] long beautiful perfect jewels.” (14d-16)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
